import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from IPython.display import display, Image
from PIL import Image as PILImage
from io import BytesIO

def notebook_dp_image(path: str, dim: set) -> None:
    img = PILImage.open(path)
    resized_img = img.resize(dim)  # (Width, Height)
    buffer = BytesIO()
    resized_img.save(buffer, format='PNG')
    display(Image(data=buffer.getvalue()))

import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras import layers, Input, Model
from tensorflow.keras.datasets import mnist
from tensorflow.keras.utils import to_categorical
from tensorflow.keras.initializers import HeNormal
print(tf.config.list_physical_devices('GPU'))

[PhysicalDevice(name='/physical_device:GPU:0', device_type='GPU')]
In[5]:
(x_train, y_train), (x_test, y_test) = mnist.load_data()
x_train = x_train.astype("float32") / 255.0
x_test = x_test.astype("float32") / 255.0

#   
x_train = x_train[..., tf.newaxis]
x_test = x_test[..., tf.newaxis]

# one-hot vectors 
y_train = to_categorical(y_train, num_classes=10)
y_test = to_categorical(y_test, num_classes=10)

x_train.shape, y_train.shape
Out[5]:
((60000, 28, 28, 1), (60000, 10))
In[7]:
initializer = HeNormal()

# functional API
inputs = Input(shape=(28, 28, 1), name="input_layer")

x = layers.Conv2D(16, (3, 3), activation="relu", name="conv1", kernel_initializer=initializer)(inputs)
x = layers.Conv2D(32, (3, 3), activation="relu", name="conv2", kernel_initializer=initializer)(x)
x = layers.Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation="relu", name="conv3", kernel_initializer=initializer)(x)
x = layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2), name="maxpool")(x)
# x = layers.Dropout(0.25, name="dropout1")(x)

x = layers.Flatten(name="flatten")(x)

x = layers.Dense(128, activation="relu", name="affine1", kernel_initializer=initializer)(x)
x = layers.Dropout(0.5, name="dropout1")(x)

x = layers.Dense(128, activation="relu", name="affine2", kernel_initializer=initializer)(x)
x = layers.Dropout(0.5, name="dropout2")(x)

outputs = layers.Dense(10, activation="softmax", name="output_layer", kernel_initializer=initializer)(x)

model = Model(inputs=inputs, outputs=outputs, name="mnist_cnn_functional")

#  
model.compile(
    optimizer="adam",
    loss="categorical_crossentropy",
    metrics=["accuracy"]
)

model.summary()

# Train the model
model.fit(
    x_train, y_train,
    batch_size=128,
    epochs=12,
    validation_split=0.1
)

# Evaluate on test set
test_loss, test_acc = model.evaluate(x_test, y_test)
print(f"Test accuracy: {test_acc:.4f}")
